text:
- More streamlined processes for the booking and payment of appointment;
- Timely sending of an invoice (not receipt), as clearly asked for, without the need for further follow up; 
- Better organisation in relation to coordination with the hospital on the findings of the sleep study; 
- Fuller discussion of small background abnormalities in my EEG. Explanations for such abnormalities (migraines, previous stroke or TBI) not relevant to my own situation were raised by the physician but no possible explanation for why they were seen in my case was provided.

As detailed above - better systems, organisation and efficiency, more staff who are more positive in a problem solving manner and more motivated to get patients seen sooner before they become demoralised and exhausted after all they do have a health issue which is why they visited in the first place.

X-rays on arrival for people who would appear to have broken a bone so less hanging around;

Reception should involve patients seeing someone who analyses the patients condition in a medical way rather than leaving it to an unqualified recepitonist even though she was doing her best;

Faster treatment of children so they do not become upset and fractious;

I've recently visited friends who are patients of the Royal Marsden & St George's Tooting where both individuals gave excellent accounts of the treatment they had / were receiving and spoke very highly of the skills & commitment of the staff treating them.   Sadly, I do not believe that same level of attitude and commitment was on show at the Woking Walk In Centre on the afternoon of Friday, 28th July.

Excellent care and very nice facility. Everybody very well meaning.

Admin needs some work. 
- Check-in process was very slow and a little "rabbit in headlights"; 
- I had understood you could bill through to the Cigna Envoy insurance program but ended up being sent a bill to pay directly; 
- The bill has a link where you can pay online, but it's broken; 
- I paid using the credit card payment line - but then did not receive any kind of email confirmation that the bill had been paid. Which I need, since I have to submit it to my insurance company. 
- You insist on answers in your survey that can't be answered because they're not relevant (I didn't see any nurses but you don't mark those questions as optional)
